<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,333,568]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,375,401]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body fusiform; scapular tubercles and setae ahead of rear shield margin; opisthosoma with a single middorsal ridge; genu II seta absent, empodium divided; anterolateral setae on coxisternum I (
<emphasis box="[1397,1426,417,442]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">1b</emphasis>
) absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,333,568]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
This genus consists of 6 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W." box="[607,840,500,526]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refId="ref44790" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr., Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W. (2003) Revised keys to world genera of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Indira Publishing House, Michigan, U. S. A., 244 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Amrine 
<emphasis box="[708,761,501,526]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). Two species have been recorded from Southeast Asia.
</paragraph>
